Q: Uncaught DOMException: Failed to set the &#39;adoptedStyleSheets&#39; property on &#39;ShadowRoot&#39;: Can&#39;t adopt non-constructed stylesheets A: <ul>
<li><a href="https://developers.google.com/web/updates/2019/02/constructable-stylesheets" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://developers.google.com/web/updates/2019/02/constructable-stylesheets</a></li>
<li>You must create a Constructable Sheet with <code>new CSSStyleSheet()</code></li>
</ul>
<p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false" data-console="true" data-babel="false" data-babel-preset-react="false" data-babel-preset-ts="false">
<div class="snippet-code">
<pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;style id="sourcestyle"&gt;
  h1 {
    color: green
  }
&lt;/style&gt;

&lt;my-element&gt;&lt;/my-element&gt;

&lt;script&gt;
  customElements.define('my-element', class extends HTMLElement {
    constructor() {
      const sheet = new CSSStyleSheet();
      sheet.replace(document.getElementById("sourcestyle").innerHTML);

      super() // returns this/element scope
        .attachShadow({ mode: 'open' }) // both sets and returns this.shadowRoot
        .innerHTML = `&lt;h1&gt;Hello World!&lt;/h1&gt;`;

      this.shadowRoot.adoptedStyleSheets = [sheet];
    }
  })
&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
</p>
<p>Maybe better to construct that <strong><em>re-usable</em></strong> stylesheet outside your component,<br />
and without creating a global <code>&lt;style&gt;</code></p>
<pre class="lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>  const sheet = new CSSStyleSheet();
  sheet.replace(`h1{color:green}`);
</code></pre>
<h3>Without Constructable StyleSheet</h3>
<p>(its 2020 - Constructable CSS doesn't work in all Browsers yet)</p>
<p>otherwise you might as well <em>move</em> the <code>&lt;style&gt;</code> with:<br />
(or cloneNode it when you want to re-use it)</p>
<pre class="lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>  this.shadowRoot.append(document.getElementById(&quot;sourcestyle&quot;));
</code></pre>
<p>Since it is a global sheet, you may want to disable it for the main DOM</p>
<pre><code>  &lt;style id=&quot;sourcestyle&quot; onload=&quot;this.disabled=true&quot;&gt;
    h1 {
      color: green
    }
  &lt;/style&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>and then undo the disabled once it is in a shadowDOM:</p>
<pre class="lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>  this.shadowRoot.getElementById(&quot;sourcestyle&quot;).disabled=false;
</code></pre>
